honeywell.printer.configuration.ez

Class PrintheadStatus

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.PrinterData
      • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.PrinterState
        • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.PrintheadStatus
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class PrintheadStatus
extends PrinterState
    This class handles the data from an {PH?} query as well as accessors to read the data values.

    This class supports the following possible parameters:

    ParameterDescription
    DDDPI
    MPrinthead Model
    PINSPrinthead Pins
    PTPrint Time
    TPrinthead Temperature
    TDPrinthead Width
    WPage Width
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • PrintheadStatus

        public PrintheadStatus(ConnectionBase connection)
        The default constructor will initialize the class with default values.

        Initially all of the _IsValid parameters will be false because no data has been processed. To 'populate' the values, the object must invoke @see PrinterState.queryPrinter(int) with the query response string.

        Parameters:
        connection - connection to printer

        public boolean getDPI_IsPresent()
        Indicates if getDPI() parameter is present.

        This function is useful to determine if the given parameter is supported on the current printer. Because of differences in configuration, hardware or version certain parameter may not exist and the results returned by the parameter getDPI() may not be valid.

        Returns:
        If the parameter is present and valid true, false otherwise.
        See Also:
